  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Single-Leg Pogo Jumps is an Output-phase explosiveness drill for unilateral lower-limb stiffness for sprinting, cutting, and takeoff. The athlete performs it fresh, with maximal intent, clean positions, and enough rest that every rep stays fast.","setup":["Clear the landing area and use a stable, non-slip surface.","Start with the lowest amplitude version that allows quiet contacts and clean alignment.","Place cones, box, line, or target only as needed for the variation."],"execution_steps":["Load only as much as needed to create a fast takeoff or contact.","Explode through the floor with the intended direction and posture.","Land, rebound, or stick according to the drill; end the rep the moment alignment or contact quality drops."],"coach_cues":["Hot floor.","Springy and quiet.","Tall hips.","Stop before contacts get heavy.","Single-Leg Pogo Jumps: quality beats quantity."],"breathing_cues":["Brace before the explosive effort.","Exhale naturally through the burst; do not hold breath across repeated reps.","Use the walk-back or reset time to restore calm breathing."],"common_faults":["Turning the drill into conditioning by adding too many reps or too little rest.","Counting reps after speed, posture, or landing/contact quality has dropped.","Chasing height, distance, or chaos before the athlete owns the basic version.","Progressing impact or complexity before quiet landings and alignment are consistent."],"quality_gate":["Rep looks fast, crisp, and intentional from start to finish.","Athlete can explain the target direction, cue, or landing outcome.","No pain, no uncontrolled collapse, and no visible drop-off in speed across the set.","Contacts are quiet and alignment stays consistent."],"stop_signs":["Pain, limping, dizziness, or apprehension.","Ground contacts become loud, slow, or unstable.","Athlete cannot recover enough to produce another high-speed rep."]}'::jsonb,
