  ('reactive-lateral-bound-callout', 'Blends lateral projection with a real-time decision so athletes cannot pre-plan the bound direction. It targets rapid force expression, neural drive, timing, and stiffness while avoiding the slow grind of traditional strength exercises.', 'Belongs in Output because the adaptation depends on freshness, intent, speed, and clean execution. If fatigue changes mechanics, the drill has shifted toward conditioning rather than explosiveness.', 'Place after Prepare & Access and any necessary Movement Intelligence, before heavy strength, conditioning, long sport blocks, or fatigue-heavy circuits. Use full rest so every rep stays explosive.', 'The common error is using the drill as a finisher, conditioning station, or high-rep challenge. Stop before power drops; do not chase fatigue, heavy load, random chaos, or more contacts after quality fades.', 'Scale by movement quality first: reduce impact, range, distance, speed, reaction demand, implement weight, or number of contacts before adding complexity. Progress only when output stays fast and repeatable.'),
