VALUES (
  'validation_rule',
  'explosiveness_readiness',
  NULL,
  'Explosiveness without conditioning drift or loaded-strength bleed',
  'Starts, jumps, bounds, throws, elastic contacts, COD power, and reactive output must stay in Output with high intent, low volume, and full rest — not heavy barbell/dumbbell strength, fatigue circuits, or conditioning disguised as power.',
  'Explosiveness cards span acceleration starts, elastic foot-ankle rudiments, jump and projection power, multidirectional COD, medicine-ball throws, and reactive partner drills for athletes who need to express force quickly without traditional loaded strength grinding.',
  'Power transfer depends on freshness, neural drive, stiffness, and clean mechanics. Poor placement, short rest, or high-rep challenges after quality fades raise injury risk and train slow output.',
  'Place after Prepare & Access and any necessary Movement Intelligence; use full rest between attempts; stop when speed, posture, contact, or landing quality drops; keep heavy strength and conditioning out of the same Output block.',
  'Do not program explosiveness as a finisher, conditioning station, or high-rep challenge; do not substitute loaded strength for Output; do not chase fatigue, heavy load, or random chaos after power drops.'
)
